# Command Palette Search Migration — Implementation Plan

## Overview

Replace the full-page search route (`/[slug]/search`) with a Cmd+K command palette overlay. The palette uses the existing `CommandDialog` component from `@repo/ui` and calls `/v1/search` (vector search) for entity results. It also includes static navigation items for quick page jumping. The old 10-file search system is deleted; shared constants are relocated to preserve the events table.

## Current State Analysis

**Search page**: 10 files (9 components + 1 route page) forming a self-contained cluster. Only consumer is the sidebar link at `app-sidebar.tsx:176`. The components form a tree: `page.tsx` → `OrgSearch` → `SearchPromptInput`, `SearchFilters`, `SearchResultsPanel` → `SearchResultsList`, `SearchResultCard`, `SearchEmptyState`, `SearchTabContent`. All use `useOrgSearchParams` (nuqs) and `search-constants.ts`.

**Command infrastructure**: `cmdk` v1.0.4 is installed. `packages/ui/src/components/ui/command.tsx` exports a complete `CommandDialog` component — but it has zero usages in `apps/app`. A working Cmd+K listener pattern exists in `apps/www/src/.../docs/_components/search.tsx:93-107`.

**Shared dependency**: `search-constants.ts` exports `AGE_PRESET_OPTIONS`, `dateRangeFromPreset`, and `SOURCE_TYPE_OPTIONS` which are imported by `events-table.tsx:27-31` and `use-event-filters.ts:5`. These must be relocated before the file can be deleted.

**Backend**: `/v1/search` endpoint (`apps/app/src/lib/search.ts`) is retained — it's also used by the AI answer agent (`packages/app-ai/src/org-search.ts`) and the public API contract (`packages/app-api-contract/src/contract.ts:51-62`).

### Key Discoveries:

- `CommandDialog` wraps cmdk in a Dialog with sr-only title/description — accessible out of the box (`command.tsx:32-66`)
- Entity rows navigate to `/${slug}/entities/${entity.externalId}` (`entity-row.tsx:22`) — search result `id` is `entityExternalId`, so URLs match directly
- `useActiveOrg()` returns the full org object (`{ id, slug, name, role, imageUrl }`) — use `org.slug` for URLs and `org.id` for `X-Org-ID` header
- `docs-mobile-nav.tsx:40-51` uses synthetic `KeyboardEvent` dispatch to trigger Cmd+K from a button — proven cross-component communication pattern

## Desired End State

A single `CommandPalette` component mounted in the org layout that:
- Opens on Cmd+K (or Ctrl+K on Windows/Linux) anywhere in the app
- Opens when clicking the sidebar search icon
- Shows static navigation items (Explore, Entities, Events, Sources, Jobs, Settings) filtered client-side
- Searches entities via `/v1/search` with 200ms debounce when query ≥ 2 chars
- Navigates to the selected page or entity detail on Enter/click
- Resets state on close

The old `/[slug]/search` route and all 9 search components are deleted. The events table continues to work via relocated shared constants.

### How to verify:

1. Cmd+K opens the palette from any org page
2. Sidebar search icon opens the palette
3. Typing "set" shows "Settings" in Navigation group
4. Typing an entity name shows entity results in Entities group
5. Selecting a nav item navigates to that page
6. Selecting an entity navigates to its detail page
7. Escape or clicking outside closes the palette
8. `/[slug]/search` returns 404
9. Events table filters (source, age) still work correctly

## What We're NOT Doing

- Changing the `/v1/search` backend or its schema
- Modifying the AI answer agent's search tool
- Adding vector search to the command palette (already using it via `/v1/search`)
- Adding inline entity preview in the palette (navigate to detail page instead)
- Adding recent searches or search history
- Changing the events table functionality

## Prerequisites

- **oRPC search rework** (`thoughts/shared/research/2026-04-07-search-page-orpc-rework.md`) must be completed first. That work fixes oRPC standards compliance in the search endpoint, which this plan's `fetch("/v1/search")` call depends on.

## Implementation Approach

Three phases: build the new component, wire it in, delete the old system. Each phase is independently testable.

---

## Phase 1: Create Command Palette Component

### Overview

Create a new `CommandPalette` client component that uses `CommandDialog`, registers a global Cmd+K listener, shows navigation items, and debounce-searches entities via `/v1/search`.

### Changes Required:

#### 1. New Component

**File**: `apps/app/src/components/command-palette.tsx` (new)

```tsx
"use client";

import { useActiveOrg } from "@repo/app-trpc/hooks";
import type { SearchResponse } from "@repo/app-validation";
import {
  CommandDialog,
  CommandEmpty,
  CommandGroup,
  CommandInput,
  CommandItem,
  CommandList,
  CommandSeparator,
} from "@repo/ui/components/ui/command";
import {
  Activity,
  Boxes,
  Briefcase,
  Loader2,
  MessageSquare,
  Plug,
  Settings,
} from "lucide-react";
import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";
import { useCallback, useEffect, useRef, useState } from "react";

interface NavItem {
  title: string;
  href: string;
  icon: React.ComponentType<{ className?: string }>;
  keywords: string[];
}

function getNavItems(orgSlug: string): NavItem[] {
  return [
    {
      title: "Explore",
      href: `/${orgSlug}`,
      icon: MessageSquare,
      keywords: ["chat", "ask", "ai", "answer"],
    },
    {
      title: "Entities",
      href: `/${orgSlug}/entities`,
      icon: Boxes,
      keywords: ["objects", "resources", "infrastructure"],
    },
    {
      title: "Events",
      href: `/${orgSlug}/events`,
      icon: Activity,
      keywords: ["logs", "activity", "webhook"],
    },
    {
      title: "Sources",
      href: `/${orgSlug}/sources`,
      icon: Plug,
      keywords: ["integrations", "connections", "providers"],
    },
    {
      title: "Jobs",
      href: `/${orgSlug}/jobs`,
      icon: Briefcase,
      keywords: ["tasks", "background", "workers"],
    },
    {
      title: "Settings",
      href: `/${orgSlug}/settings`,
      icon: Settings,
      keywords: ["preferences", "config", "api", "keys"],
    },
  ];
}

export function CommandPalette() {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);
  const [query, setQuery] = useState("");
  const [results, setResults] = useState<SearchResponse["results"]>([]);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
  const abortRef = useRef<AbortController | null>(null);
  const router = useRouter();
  const activeOrg = useActiveOrg();

  const orgSlug = activeOrg?.slug ?? "";
  const clerkOrgId = activeOrg?.id ?? "";
  const navItems = getNavItems(orgSlug);

  // Cmd+K global listener (capture phase, same pattern as docs search)
  useEffect(() => {
    function handleKeyDown(e: KeyboardEvent) {
      if (e.isComposing) return;
      if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === "k") {
        e.preventDefault();
        setOpen((prev) => !prev);
      }
    }
    document.addEventListener("keydown", handleKeyDown, true);
    return () => document.removeEventListener("keydown", handleKeyDown, true);
  }, []);

  // Reset state on close
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!open) {
      setQuery("");
      setResults([]);
      abortRef.current?.abort();
    }
  }, [open]);

  // Debounced entity search via /v1/search
  useEffect(() => {
    if (query.length < 2 || !clerkOrgId) {
      setResults([]);
      return;
    }

    const timer = setTimeout(() => {
      abortRef.current?.abort();
      abortRef.current = new AbortController();
      setIsLoading(true);

      fetch("/v1/search", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: {
          "Content-Type": "application/json",
          "X-Org-ID": clerkOrgId,
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({ query, limit: 10 }),
        signal: abortRef.current.signal,
      })
        .then((res) => res.json())
        .then((data: SearchResponse) => {
          setResults(data.results);
          setIsLoading(false);
        })
        .catch((err: unknown) => {
          if (err instanceof Error && err.name === "AbortError") return;
          setIsLoading(false);
        });
    }, 200);

    return () => clearTimeout(timer);
  }, [query, clerkOrgId]);

  // Cleanup abort controller on unmount
  useEffect(() => {
    return () => {
      abortRef.current?.abort();
    };
  }, []);

  const handleSelect = useCallback(
    (href: string) => {
      setOpen(false);
      router.push(href);
    },
    [router]
  );

  // Filter nav items client-side when query is present
  const filteredNav = query
    ? navItems.filter(
        (item) =>
          item.title.toLowerCase().includes(query.toLowerCase()) ||
          item.keywords.some((kw) => kw.includes(query.toLowerCase()))
      )
    : navItems;

  return (
    <CommandDialog
      description="Search entities or navigate to a page"
      onOpenChange={setOpen}
      open={open}
      shouldFilter={false}
      title="Command Palette"
    >
      <CommandInput
        onValueChange={setQuery}
        placeholder="Search entities or jump to..."
        value={query}
      />
      <CommandList className="max-h-[min(400px,50vh)]">
        <CommandEmpty>No results found.</CommandEmpty>

        {filteredNav.length > 0 && (
          <CommandGroup heading="Navigation">
            {filteredNav.map((item) => (
              <CommandItem
                key={item.href}
                onSelect={() => handleSelect(item.href)}
              >
                <item.icon className="mr-2 size-4" />
                {item.title}
              </CommandItem>
            ))}
          </CommandGroup>
        )}

        {query.length >= 2 && (
          <>
            <CommandSeparator />
            <CommandGroup heading="Entities">
              {isLoading && results.length === 0 && (
                <div className="flex items-center justify-center py-6">
                  <Loader2 className="size-4 animate-spin text-muted-foreground" />
                </div>
              )}
              {results.map((result) => (
                <CommandItem
                  key={result.id}
                  onSelect={() =>
                    handleSelect(`/${orgSlug}/entities/${result.id}`)
                  }
                >
                  <div className="flex flex-col gap-0.5">
                    <span className="text-sm">{result.title}</span>
                    {result.snippet && (
                      <span className="line-clamp-1 text-muted-foreground text-xs">
                        {result.snippet}
                      </span>
                    )}
                  </div>
                </CommandItem>
              ))}
            </CommandGroup>
          </>
        )}
      </CommandList>
    </CommandDialog>
  );
}
```

### Success Criteria:

#### Automated Verification:

- [ ] Type checking passes: `pnpm typecheck`
- [ ] Linting passes: `pnpm check`

#### Manual Verification:

- [ ] Component renders without errors when imported (test in isolation before wiring)

**Implementation Note**: After completing this phase and all automated verification passes, pause here for manual confirmation before proceeding to Phase 2.

---

## Phase 2: Integrate into App Layout + Update Sidebar

### Overview

Mount the `CommandPalette` in the org layout and change the sidebar search button from a navigation link to a button that opens the palette via synthetic Cmd+K event dispatch.

### Changes Required:

#### 1. Mount in Org Layout

**File**: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/layout.tsx`
**Changes**: Import and render `<CommandPalette />` as a sibling of `<AppSidebar />` inside `<SidebarProvider>`.

```tsx
// Add import at top (after line 9):
import { CommandPalette } from "~/components/command-palette";

// Add component inside SidebarProvider (after line 53):
<SidebarProvider className="!h-full !min-h-0 overflow-hidden bg-sidebar">
  <AppSidebar />
  <CommandPalette />
  {/* Right column... */}
</SidebarProvider>
```

#### 2. Update Sidebar Search Button

**File**: `apps/app/src/components/app-sidebar.tsx`
**Changes**: Replace the `<Link>` to `/search` with a `<button>` that dispatches a synthetic Cmd+K KeyboardEvent. Remove `Link` import if no longer needed (it's still used by other nav items, so keep it). Remove `asChild` from the Button since it no longer wraps a Link.

Replace lines 169-179:

```tsx
{/* Before (Link to search page): */}
<Button
  asChild
  className="h-6 w-6 rounded-full text-muted-foreground"
  size="icon"
  title="Search"
  variant="ghost"
>
  <Link href={{ pathname: `/${orgSlug}/search` }} prefetch={true}>
    <Search className="size-3.5" />
  </Link>
</Button>

{/* After (button that opens command palette): */}
<Button
  className="h-6 w-6 rounded-full text-muted-foreground"
  onClick={() => {
    document.dispatchEvent(
      new KeyboardEvent("keydown", {
        key: "k",
        metaKey: true,
        bubbles: true,
        cancelable: true,
        composed: true,
      })
    );
  }}
  size="icon"
  title="Search (⌘K)"
  variant="ghost"
>
  <Search className="size-3.5" />
</Button>
```

This uses the synthetic event dispatch pattern proven in `apps/www/src/.../docs/_components/docs-mobile-nav.tsx:40-51`. No prop drilling or context needed — the sidebar fires a synthetic Cmd+K event that the `CommandPalette` listener picks up.

### Success Criteria:

#### Automated Verification:

- [ ] Type checking passes: `pnpm typecheck`
- [ ] Linting passes: `pnpm check`
- [ ] Build passes: `pnpm build:app`

#### Manual Verification:

- [ ] Cmd+K opens the command palette from any org page
- [ ] Clicking the sidebar search icon opens the command palette
- [ ] Typing a nav item name (e.g. "set") filters the Navigation group to "Settings"
- [ ] Typing an entity query (≥ 2 chars) shows entity results after ~200ms
- [ ] Selecting a nav item navigates to that page and closes the palette
- [ ] Selecting an entity navigates to `/[slug]/entities/[externalId]`
- [ ] Escape closes the palette
- [ ] Clicking outside the palette closes it
- [ ] Cmd+K toggles the palette open/closed
- [ ] State resets (query cleared, results cleared) when palette closes

**Implementation Note**: After completing this phase and all manual verification passes, proceed to Phase 3 cleanup.

---

## Phase 3: Delete Old Search System

### Overview

Remove the 10 search-page files, relocate shared constants used by the events table, and delete the now-unused `search-constants.ts`.

### Changes Required:

#### 1. Relocate Shared Constants

**File**: `apps/app/src/lib/filter-constants.ts` (new)
**Changes**: Move `AGE_PRESET_OPTIONS`, `dateRangeFromPreset`, and `SOURCE_TYPE_OPTIONS` from `search-constants.ts`. These are generic filter utilities, not search-specific.

```tsx
import { PROVIDER_DISPLAY } from "@repo/app-providers/client";

export const SOURCE_TYPE_OPTIONS = Object.entries(PROVIDER_DISPLAY).map(
  ([value, entry]) => ({ value, label: entry.displayName })
);

export const AGE_PRESET_OPTIONS = [
  { value: "1h", label: "1 hour" },
  { value: "6h", label: "6 hours" },
  { value: "24h", label: "24 hours" },
  { value: "72h", label: "3 days" },
  { value: "7d", label: "7 days" },
  { value: "30d", label: "30 days" },
  { value: "none", label: "No limit" },
] as const;

export function dateRangeFromPreset(preset: string): {
  after?: string;
} {
  if (preset === "none") {
    return {};
  }
  const hoursMap: Record<string, number> = {
    "1h": 1,
    "6h": 6,
    "24h": 24,
    "72h": 72,
    "7d": 168,
    "30d": 720,
  };
  const hours = hoursMap[preset];
  if (!hours) {
    return {};
  }
  const after = new Date(Date.now() - hours * 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString();
  return { after };
}
```

#### 2. Update Events Table Imports

**File**: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/(manage)/events/_components/events-table.tsx`
**Changes**: Update import path from `~/components/search-constants` to `~/lib/filter-constants` (line 27-31).

```tsx
// Before:
import {
  AGE_PRESET_OPTIONS,
  dateRangeFromPreset,
  SOURCE_TYPE_OPTIONS,
} from "~/components/search-constants";

// After:
import {
  AGE_PRESET_OPTIONS,
  dateRangeFromPreset,
  SOURCE_TYPE_OPTIONS,
} from "~/lib/filter-constants";
```

**File**: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/(manage)/events/_components/use-event-filters.ts`
**Changes**: Update import path (line 5).

```tsx
// Before:
import { AGE_PRESET_OPTIONS } from "~/components/search-constants";

// After:
import { AGE_PRESET_OPTIONS } from "~/lib/filter-constants";
```

#### 3. Delete Search Page Files

Delete these 11 files:

```
apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/search/page.tsx
apps/app/src/components/org-search.tsx
apps/app/src/components/use-org-search-params.ts
apps/app/src/components/search-constants.ts
apps/app/src/components/search-filters.tsx
apps/app/src/components/search-prompt-input.tsx
apps/app/src/components/search-results-panel.tsx
apps/app/src/components/search-results-list.tsx
apps/app/src/components/search-result-card.tsx
apps/app/src/components/search-empty-state.tsx
apps/app/src/components/search-tab-content.tsx
```

### Success Criteria:

#### Automated Verification:

- [ ] Type checking passes: `pnpm typecheck`
- [ ] Linting passes: `pnpm check`
- [ ] Build passes: `pnpm build:app`
- [ ] No references to deleted files: `grep -r "search-constants\|org-search\|search-filters\|search-prompt-input\|search-results-panel\|search-results-list\|search-result-card\|search-empty-state\|search-tab-content\|use-org-search-params" apps/app/src/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"` returns nothing

#### Manual Verification:

- [ ] `/[slug]/search` returns 404
- [ ] Events page source filter dropdown works
- [ ] Events page age filter dropdown works
- [ ] AI answer agent search tool still works (ask a question in Explore that triggers search)

**Implementation Note**: After completing this phase and all verification passes, the migration is complete.

---

## Testing Strategy

### Manual Testing Steps:

1. Open the app, press Cmd+K — palette opens
2. Type "enti" — "Entities" shows in Navigation group
3. Clear input, type a known entity name — entity results appear after brief delay
4. Press Enter on an entity result — navigates to entity detail page
5. Press Escape — palette closes, state resets
6. Click sidebar search icon — palette opens
7. Navigate to `/[slug]/search` directly — 404
8. Go to Events page — source and age filters work normally
9. Go to Explore, ask a question — AI answer agent search tool returns results

## Performance Considerations

- **Debounce**: 200ms delay before firing `/v1/search` prevents excessive API calls during typing
- **AbortController**: In-flight requests are cancelled when query changes or palette closes
- **No preloading**: Search only fires when query ≥ 2 chars, no wasted requests on open
- **Client-side nav filtering**: Navigation items are filtered in-memory with no network calls
- **CommandDialog**: Renders as a portal, doesn't affect DOM layout of the app

## References

- Research document: `thoughts/shared/research/2026-04-07-command-palette-search-migration.md`
- CommandDialog component: `packages/ui/src/components/ui/command.tsx:32-66`
- Existing Cmd+K pattern: `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(content)/docs/_components/search.tsx:93-107`
- Synthetic event dispatch pattern: `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(content)/docs/_components/docs-mobile-nav.tsx:40-51`
- Org layout mount point: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/layout.tsx:52-68`
- Sidebar search button: `apps/app/src/components/app-sidebar.tsx:169-179`
- Entity row navigation pattern: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/(manage)/entities/_components/entity-row.tsx:22`
- `/v1/search` backend: `apps/app/src/lib/search.ts:15-129`
- Events table (shared constants consumer): `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/(manage)/events/_components/events-table.tsx:27-31`
- oRPC search rework (prerequisite): `thoughts/shared/research/2026-04-07-search-page-orpc-rework.md`

---

## Improvement Log

**2026-04-07 — Adversarial review (`/improve_plan`)**

Changes made:

1. **Added Prerequisites section** — oRPC search rework must be completed before this plan. The `/v1/search` endpoint needs oRPC standards compliance first.

2. **Fixed `clerkOrgId` empty-string bug** — `useActiveOrg()` can return `null`, causing `""` to be passed as `X-Org-ID` which the oRPC middleware rejects with a 401. Added guard: `if (query.length < 2 || !clerkOrgId)` in the search effect.

3. **Simplified slug extraction** — Replaced `pathname.split("/").filter(Boolean)[0]` with `activeOrg?.slug ?? ""`. The `useActiveOrg()` hook already resolves the org from URL params — no need for redundant pathname parsing. Removed `usePathname` import.

4. **Fixed loading indicator visibility** — Loading spinner was inside `CommandEmpty`, which only renders when zero `CommandItem` children exist. If nav items matched the query, `CommandEmpty` never rendered and the search loading state was invisible. Moved loading spinner into the Entities `CommandGroup` so it shows independently of nav item filtering.

5. **Increased `CommandList` max-height** — Default `max-h-[300px]` left ~100px for entity results after 6 nav items. Changed to `max-h-[min(400px,50vh)]` for better search result visibility.

No spike run — `shouldFilter={false}` with async results is well-documented cmdk behavior, low risk.
